<HEADLINE>
FT  03 MAY 94 / World News in Brief: Grand prix deaths prompt emergency
probe into safety
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
An emergency meeting to consider Formula One safety following the deaths of
grand prix drivers Ayrton Senna and Roland Ratzenberger has been called by
the world governing body of motor sport, the Federation Internationale de
l'Automobile. The move to ascertain the precise causes of the double tragedy
came as tributes were paid around the world to Senna, the 34-year-old triple
world champion from Sao Paulo. Brazil's president Itamar Franco declared
three days of national mourning for Senna, who died of head injuries when
his Renault-Williams car left the track at 180mph during Sunday's San Marino
Grand Prix at Imola.
