<HEADLINE>
FT  03 MAY 94 / Observer: Oh golly
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pretoria-Witwatersrand-Vereeniging hardly trips off even a South African
tongue. Hence the search for a more euphonic handle to fit the sprawling
conurbation around Johannesburg, one of the nine new provinces. 'Egoli',
meaning 'place of gold', and the name given to Jo-burg by black mineworkers,
was an early suggestion. But then, what would non-white residents of Egoli
be called? Quite. The search continues.
</TEXT>
