FT  03 MAY 94 / Business Travel (Update): Mailbox
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
In May AT&amp;T launches what it claims is the first international mailbox
service for travellers wanting a 24-hour base for receiving and sending
messages and faxes wherever they may be.
The US operator's new service, called WorldPlus, gives subscribers a mailbox
and service centre accessed via touch-tone or voice-response.
In addition to storing and replaying messages, WorldPlus allows users to
reply to the number from which a message has been received at the flick of a
button, and to send multiple messages and faxes as instructed. Subscribers
pay Pounds 50 a year standing charge, then pay for services on a usage
basis. The charge for messages and faxes is flat-rate.
