<HEADLINE>
FT  03 MAY 94 / Industrial recovery gains pace
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER MARSH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The economic recovery is strengthening, say two reports out today. They
report that manufacturers are increasing output and investment, and the
outlook for new businesses is improving.
A sharp increase in orders and production is reported by the Chartered
Institute of Purchasing and Supply, while the Confederation of British
Industry says employment and investment among small manufacturers should
rise strongly during the next few months.
In a third survey, venture capital group 3i is positive about recovery
prospects, though it says a majority of small companies believe interest
rates will rise during the next year because of the need to combat
inflation.
According to the Chartered Institute of Purchasing and Supply, which every
month asks purchasing managers how they see industrial trends, manufacturing
activity increased last month at its fastest rate since the survey began
three years ago.
Improved demand, helped by an increase in marketing activity, led to a large
rise in orders. Delivery times across industry increased significantly
because suppliers were busier.
Stocks of purchases and finished goods fell sharply in April compared with
March. That reflected the success by many manufacturers and suppliers in
shifting products more quickly from their warehouses to customers.
Manufacturing recruitment increased in April for the third successive month.
The report from the CBI, conducted jointly with Pannell Kerr Forster, a
consultancy, also points to brightening economic prospects. Mr John Parsons,
chairman of the CBI's smaller firms council, said it provided more evidence
that small businesses were 'leading the economic recovery'.
Total orders for small manufacturing groups rose sharply last month and are
expected to show a further rise during the summer. More small businesses
than at any time since July 1988 say they will step up spending on plant and
machinery over the next year.
Monthly Trends. Chartered Institute of Purchasing and Supply, 0491 574671.
Small Firms Report, CBI, 103 New Oxford St, London WC1A 1DU, Pounds 20.
Economic Report. 3i, 91 Waterloo Rd, London SE1 8XP.
</TEXT>
