FT  03 MAY 94 / N Sea platform 'blasts' probed
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Engineers last night flew to the Piper Bravo platform 120 miles north-east
of Aberdeen in the North Sea's Claymore field to investigate reports of
minor explosions.
No one on board the platform was injured, although 98 non-essential
personnel were evacuated by helicopter as a precaution.
Elf Enterprise Caledonia, operator of the platform which is the successor to
ill-fated Piper Alpha, said that there was no explosion in the sense of a
fire or blast but the engineers would be investigating unconfirmed reports
of 'noises within the pipework related to the flare system' which burns off
excess gas.
'Production from the Piper field and its satellite field was immediately
shut down,' Elf said.
