FT  03 MAY 94 / Bank staff plan 2 1/2-hour strike
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
About 100 staff of Barclays Bank in Birmingham are planning a 2 1/2 -hour
strike today.
The staff, members of the finance union Bifu, who work at Barclays
Centralised Securities Office in Summer Road, Birmingham, are protesting at
the withdrawal of protection for their salaries following a reorganisation
at Barclays. The union claims the reorganisation has left many staff working
in lower paid grades.
Mr Terry Bray, Bifu organiser in the west Midlands, said: 'Our members have
co-operated with endless changes in Barclays and they should not be
penalised in their pay packets. Yet some of our members stand to lose more
than Pounds 5,000 over the next few years.'
