FT  30 APR 94 / Maxwell pensions sue Goldman: International News Digest
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK HARVERSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Trustees for two Maxwell Communications pension schemes last night filed
lawsuits in New York against Goldman Sachs, charging that the US investment
bank was negligent in allowing Mr Kevin Maxwell in 1991 to transfer millions
of pounds from the pension funds to companies controlled by the Maxwell
family.
The lawsuits, filed by MCP Pension Trustees and MGN Pension Trustees, seek
punitive damages against Goldman and compensation of Dollars 47m (Pounds
31m), the amount the trustees claim Mr Maxwell appropriated from the funds
with Goldman's aid.
Goldman said the claims against it were 'without merit' and represented an
'expensive and time-consuming distraction.'
