</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Norwich Union, one of Britain's biggest insurers, became the second company
in three days to receive a Pounds 300,000 fine from life insurance industry
watchdog Lautro. The fine was imposed for breakdowns in management control
relating particularly to the implementation of higher training and
competence standards. The regulator was also concerned about recruitment
procedures and 'fact finds'  - the checking of information gathered by sales
agents. It said the failures 'had risks for potential customers'. Page 22;
PIA chief warns on disclosure, Page 4; Finance and the Family, Wkd VII
